    <text id="B1235T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Brower asks for transportation to Staunton for a Ben Beal, who had surgery at
                    Howard's Grove Hospital in Richmond.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Office Howard's Grove
                    Hospital,
                    <name type="recipient">Surgeon J. J. DeLamater, U.S.S.<lb/>Surgeon in Chief
                            <abbr expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">B.R.F.
                            &amp; A.L.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-04-05">April 5th, 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to request transportation to Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia"
                    >Va.</abbr> for Ben Beal, <add hand="h1" place="inline">freedman</add> a patient
                    in this Hospital successfully operated on for Cataract.</p>

                <p>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr> is his home and if he is transported
                    there, the Government will be relieved of his support.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient Servant">Obed't
                        Serv't</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>D.R. Brower<lb/>A.A. Surgeon in Charge<lb/>Howard's Grove
                    Hospital</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
